<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="412" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">
Taxonomic notes. The two specimens obtained here are regarded as conspecific because of their morphological similarity. They clearly belong to the 
<taxonomicName box="[575,676,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="equestris">
<emphasis box="[575,676,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">equestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Marcos-Garcia, M. A. &amp; Vujic, A. &amp; Ricarte, A. &amp; Stahls, G." box="[764,1065,188,213]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Marcos-Garcia" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" pagination="332 - 348" part="143" refId="ref15210" refString="Marcos-Garcia, M. A., Vujic, A., Ricarte, A. &amp; Stahls, G. (2011) Towards an integrated taxonomy of the Merodon equestris complex (Diptera: Syrphidae) including description of a new species, with additional data on Iberian Merodon. The Canadian Entomologist, 143, 332 - 348." title="Towards an integrated taxonomy of the Merodon equestris complex (Diptera: Syrphidae) including description of a new species, with additional data on Iberian Merodon" type="journal article" year="2011">
Marcos-García 
<emphasis box="[941,998,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1006,1065,188,212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). They are not 
<taxonomicName box="[1235,1340,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavus">
<emphasis box="[1235,1340,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">M. flavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because they have a conspicuous bulge in the metatibia and different male genitalia. Specimens are more similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="equestris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">M. equestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[313,452,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis box="[313,452,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">M. confusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It might be that our two specimens belong to the same cryptic taxon referred to in 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcos-Garcia, M. A. &amp; Vujic, A. &amp; Ricarte, A. &amp; Stahls, G." box="[151,462,295,320]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Marcos-Garcia" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" pagination="332 - 348" part="143" refId="ref15210" refString="Marcos-Garcia, M. A., Vujic, A., Ricarte, A. &amp; Stahls, G. (2011) Towards an integrated taxonomy of the Merodon equestris complex (Diptera: Syrphidae) including description of a new species, with additional data on Iberian Merodon. The Canadian Entomologist, 143, 332 - 348." title="Towards an integrated taxonomy of the Merodon equestris complex (Diptera: Syrphidae) including description of a new species, with additional data on Iberian Merodon" type="journal article" year="2011">
Marcos-García 
<emphasis box="[326,375,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[397,455,296,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as intermediate 
<taxonomicName box="[646,744,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis box="[646,744,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">confusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName box="[752,853,297,320]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="equestris">
<emphasis box="[752,853,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">equestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
